EDIT A REPLICATED DATABASE

This form is used to define a database that is part of your replication
scheme.

To make a change, use the Tab key to move to the desired field and enter
the new value.  To save the changed definition, select the Save
operation.

The fields on the form are:

        FIELD NAME              DESCRIPTION
        ----------              -----------
        Database Number         This is a unique system-wide identifier
                                assigned previously.  It cannot be
                                changed.

        Virtual Node Name       A mandatory field to specify the virtual
                                node (vnode) name, as defined in the
                                Ingres/Net netutil utility, used
                                to connect to the database.

        Database Name           The name of the database.  If this is
                                local database, this cannot be changed.

        Database Owner          The owner (DBA) of the database.

        DBMS Type               The type of DBMS, for example,
                                Ingres or CA-Datacom.  Use
                                ListChoices to view acceptable values.

        Remarks                 A short comment.


The menu commands are as follows:

        MENU COMMAND    SYNOPSIS
        ------------    --------
        Save            Save the definition and return to the Database
                        Summary screen.

        ListChoices     Display a list of acceptable values for the
                        current field.

        Help            Access the Help facility.

        End             Return to the Database Summary screen.
